<br>
Also, as was said earlier. Maybe a Raid is about loot, but that is definitly not the reason many people go. Esp if you go look at the Open Raids from early on. There is NO GROUP for the wizards to be  making stronger in Hate. There is no Guild called Open Raid. It's not a close knit group of 24 friends. It's about 150 people who go to these things (not at the same time). Maybe someone who does win a roll continues on, but there is zero guarantee that they will, so there is NO incentive for the wizards to go. And then there are all the times that some high levels have helped out my guild on raids...raids that their guild did about three months ago. There are two people in particular that I can think of whose guilds are doing planes and better raids...yet they came back to help us do City of Mist and Chardok. There was not one single thing that they needed from those places, so maybe PA was raiding for gear...but they sure weren't.<br>
