<br>
I do disagree with Tzaroth on raids being completely about loot.  Ryael/skrag/whatever it is this week, I mean come on.  I'd go on a raid to anything if I had the chance, because I've never seen it.  I know every newbie zone in the joint, and it's old hat...I'd gladly welcome seeing a plane, any plane.<br>
<br>
Why the guilds keep going back is so that they can see new things!  You go in a place once, it has nice drops, everyone's seen it, etc.  Now to go to the next NEW thing, more people need the gear that's dropped in the OLD place.  So you have to keep doing what's there until you can move to the next place.<br>
<br>
Look at it from a real life perspective...when you get a job (assuming you've ever had one), do you quit after you get the first paycheck?  No.  You spend the next paycheck on different stuff.  Alot of people work to continue their education so that they can have better careers.  This is the same thing that happens with raiding guilds...they have to get enough members with good gear so that when they go to the next place on the list, they won't wipe out and ruin everyone's day.<br>
<br>
I'd easily go on an open raid if I could just to see new things.  If I joined a raiding guild that could take me places that open raids could never go, I'd fully expect to help them farm things just so I could see the next best thing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufaira.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faira</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/14/02 1:26:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=57>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How bout someone saying- Congratulations</span><hr size=1> I hardly ever post on this board, but this got my eye...let me quote:<br>
